direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods validate unique identification numbers (CNPJ and CPF) using similar algorithms and structures.
The cnpj method generates CNPJ numbers and relies on isCNPJValid for validation, making it a direct dependency.
The cpf method generates CPF numbers and shares similar logic with the CNPJ generation, making it a candidate for cross-validation.
Both isCNPJValid and isCPFValid use the unmask method to prepare the input for validation, indicating shared resource access.
Both isCNPJValid and isCPFValid use the calculateWeight method to compute validation checksums, sharing a similar internal structure.
Both isCNPJValid and isCPFValid use the digit method to finalize the validation checksum, sharing a similar internal structure.
